		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    <B>* Everlore's Guide to Fletching</b></b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:BrandonP@obsidian-tech.com">Dieciden (Brandon Parker)</a> | 
		            8/26/1999 5:33:03 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2"><table border="0" cellspacing="1" width="594">
    <tr>
      <td width="100%" height="235">

<p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b><a name="Fletching">Fletching</a></b></font>:</p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Introduction:">Introduction:</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#What you need to buy to fletch:">What
    you need to buy to fletch:</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Arrows:">Arrows</a>:</font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Where to buy fletching components:">Where
    to buy fletching components:</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#How to make your first arrow:">How
    to make your first arrow:</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#How to calculate your arrow statistics:">How
    to calculate your arrows statistics:</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#The Fetching Guide Book:">The
    Fletching Guide Book:</a></font></li>
</ul>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="Introduction:">Introduction:</a></b></font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Fletching is a very complicated skill in which
to undertake, but you will come away with the knowledge of how to make bows and
arrow better than any you can buy off a vender. However reaching that level of
skill will take much time, practice, and money. But it is well worth the effort.
The very first that you need to do when you decide to become a Fletcher is
invest at least 10 practice points into you fetching skill. This is Everlore's policy
with all trade skills, simply because it will save you money, time, and
components. </font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="What you need to buy to fletch:">What
you need to buy to fletch:</a></b></font></p>
<div align="center">
  <table border="0" cellspacing="1" width="100%" bordercolorlight="#C0C0C0" bordercolordark="#666666">
    <tr>
      <td width="77%" rowspan="3" valign="top" align="left"><font face="Verdana" size="2">The
        very first thing you must purchase is a fletching kit. This is what you
        will be making all your bows and arrows in. You should also buy the
        fletching guide book, but we will include the whole of the text of this
        book with in this guide so it is not necessary. Now you need to buy the
        components for the first item you intend to make. And we advise that the
        first items you attempt to make be <a href="#Arrows:">arrows</a>.</font>
        <p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="Arrows:">Arrows</a></b><a name="Arrows:">: </a></font></td>
      <td width="14%" align="center">Item:</td>
      <td width="9%" align="center">Picture:</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width="14%" align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Fletching Kit</font></td>
      <td width="9%" align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Fletchig%20kit.jpg" width="50" height="49"></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width="14%" align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Fletching Book</font></td>
      <td width="9%" align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Book.jpg" width="49" height="49"></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2">There
are four parts to every arrow. <a href="#Nocks:">Groove Nocks</a>, <a href="#Shafts:">Shafts</a>,
<a href="#Tips:">Tips</a>, and <a href="#Fletches:">Fletches</a>. And you will
need one of each part for every arrow that you make. Now there are different qualities
for each part, and the better the quality of the part, the harder it will be to
make an arrow with that part. And consequently the better the quality of the
part the more expensive it will be to buy. Here is a break down of each part and
how difficult it is to make an arrow with that part.</font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0" align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Fletching">Top</a></font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0" align="center"> </p>
