			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a level 10 Dwarf Rogue. I started fletching at level 9 (had to buy the kit from an elf vendor). I started with 10 pracs in fletching and began with making the cheapest arrows. I sell my arrows to players at just over cost so I can continue making new arrows. My skill is now at 73 and I am making arrows that cost 384cp per 5 to make. I'm trying to gather info on making bows, but I think making arrows is the way to increase your skill easily. I have had very little difficulty  selling my arrows in the Butcherblock area, and only recently have I started having a decent number of failures. (Yeah, now that it costs me more to fail. :( ) To anyone thinking about fletching I say &quot;Go for it!&quot; I think making arrows is a lot of fun, and I get to meet a lot of people new people. Only tradeskill I've tried where even the low level makes were easy to sell.<BR>
<BR>
The little dwarf that could
				</font>
			</td>

